Added slcDevPortCfgCHAPAuthLocalUsers, slcDevPortCfgUseSites, slcPCCardCfgCHAPAuthLocalUsers, slcPCCardCfgUseSites, slcDevUSBCfgCHAPAuthLocalUsers, slcDevUSBCfgUseSites, and the slcServSite section.

Added slcServSNMPv3ReadWriteUser, slcServSNMPv3Security, slcServSNMPv3Authentication, slcServSNMPv3Encryption, slcServHostList objects, slcAuthNISEscapeSeq, slcAuthNISBreakSeq, slcAuthLDAPEscapeSeq, slcAuthLDAPBreakSeq, slcAuthRADIUSEscapeSeq, slcAuthRADIUSBreakSeq, slcAuthKerbEscapeSeq, slcAuthKerbBreakSeq, slcAuthTACACSEscapeSeq, slcAuthTACACSBreakSeq, slcAuthRemoteUserEscapeSeq, slcAuthRemoteUserBreakSeq, slcDevConShowLines, slcDevPortCfgHostList, slcPCCardCfgHostList, slcDevPortCfgDevLowTemp, slcDevPortCfgDevHighTemp, slcDevPortCfgDevTemperature, slcDevPortCfgDevLowHumidity, slcDevPortCfgDevHighHumidity, slcDevPortCfgDevHumidity, slcDevPortCfgDevTraps, slcDevPortCfgShowLines, slcSystemWebGadget, slcSystemAction, slcEventDevicePortDevice* notifications.

Added slcNetEthAlternateGateway, slcNetEthPingIPAddress, slcNetEthPingInterface, slcNetEthPingDelay, slcNetEthPingFailed, slcServSNMPTrapCommunity, slcServSNMPAlarmDelay, slcServPhoneHome section, slcDevPortCfgWebColumns, slcDevPortCfgWebRows and slcDevPortCfgSyslogState.

Added slcNetFirewallRuleset* objects, slcNetFirewallMapping* objects, slcAuthLDAPEncrypt, slcAuthTACACSServer2, slcAuthTACACSServer3, slcDevPortCfgDODAuth, slcDevPortCfgDODCHAPHost, slcPCCardCfgDODAuth, and slcPCCardCfgDODCHAPHost. Added dialondemand(5) to slcDevPortCfgModemState and slcPCCardCfgModemState.

Added slcNetEthDomain, slcServNTPLocalServer2, slcServNTPLocalServer3, slcServSSHV1Incoming, slcAuthNISSlave4, slcAuthNISSlave5, slcPCCardCfgGSMPPPCompression, slcPCCardCfgGSMAutoAcquireDNS, slcPCCardCfgGSMDialoutMode, slcPCCardCfgGSMContextID, slcPCCardCfgGSMBearerService. Added SLCAuthRemote group. Added slcServAuditIncludeCLI, slcAuthLocalUserGroup, slcAuthLocalUserRights, slcAuthNISGroup, slcAuthNISRights, slcAuthNISMenu, slcAuthNISListenPorts, slcAuthNISDataPorts, slcAuthNISClearPorts, slcAuthLDAPGroup, slcAuthLDAPRights, slcAuthLDAPMenu, slcAuthLDAPListenPorts, slcAuthLDAPDataPorts, slcAuthLDAPClearPorts, slcAuthRADIUSGroup, slcAuthRADIUSRights, slcAuthRADIUSMenu, slcAuthRADIUSListenPorts, slcAuthRADIUSDataPorts, slcAuthRADIUSClearPorts, slcAuthKerbGroup, slcAuthKerbRights, slcAuthKerbMenu, slcAuthKerbListenPorts, slcAuthKerbDataPorts, slcAuthKerbClearPorts, slcAuthTACACSGroup, slcAuthTACACSRights, slcAuthTACACSMenu, slcAuthTACACSListenPorts, slcAuthTACACSDataPorts, slcAuthTACACSClearPorts, slcDevGlobalMaxDirect, slcSystemWebTimeout, slcPCCardCfgTelnetState, slcPCCardCfgTelnetPort, slcPCCardCfgTelnetAuth, slcPCCardCfgSSHState, slcPCCardCfgSSHPort, slcPCCardCfgSSHAuth, slcPCCardCfgTCPState, slcPCCardCfgTCPPort, slcPCCardCfgTCPAuth, slcPCCardCfgGSMPIN, slcPCCardCfgGSMNetworkName. Added slcEventDevicePortSLMData and slcEventDevicePortSLMConfig traps. Added Textual Convention UserGroup and UserRights. Obsoleted slcDevGlobalListenPorts, slcDevGlobalDataPorts and slcDevGlobalClearPorts.

Added slcServSSHTimeout, slcServSSHWebSSH, slcServSNMPReadOnlyCommunity, slcServSNMPReadWriteCommunity, slcDevPortCfgAction, slcDevPortCfgEmailSend, slcDevPortCfgBanner, slcPCCardCfgISDNChannel, slcPCCardCfgISDNChannelNum, slcConnDurationStr, slcConnIdle, slcConnIdleStr, slcConnSourceIP, slcSystemWelcomeBanner, slcSystemLoginBanner, slcSystemLogoutBanner. Added sftp(3) to slcSystemLoadVia.

slc.description: MIB module for managing Lantronix Secure Console Managers and Advanced Console Managers

EnabledState.name: EnabledState
EnabledState.description: The enabled/disabled state of an SLC feature.

AuthOrder.name: AuthOrder
AuthOrder.description: Authentication order for a remote authentication method. If the authentication method is disabled, AuthOrder = 0.

UserGroup.name: UserGroup
UserGroup.description: The group assigned to a user. Each group has a set of user rights associated with it.

UserRights.name: UserRights
UserRights.description: The rights assigned to a user. Each group has a set of user rights associated with it. The string is a comma-separated list of rights: ad - full administrative rights do - Device Ports operations dp - configure Device Ports dr - Diagnostics and Reports dt - configure Date and Time fc - manage Firmware and Configurations lu - configure Local Users md - configure Internal Modem nt - configure Networking pc - configure PC Card ra - configure Remote Authentication rp - manage Remote Power Managers rs - Reboot or Shutdown the SLC sd - manage SD Card sk - configure SSH Keys sn - configure Secure Ltx Network sv - configure Services ub - configure USB Devices um - configure User Menus wb - Web Access

TimeoutDataDirection.name: TimeoutDataDirection
TimeoutDataDirection.description: The direction of data used to determine if a connection has timed out.

RPMTowerIndex.name: RPMTowerIndex
RPMTowerIndex.description: The unique identifier for an RPM tower or unit.

RPMOutletIndex.name: RPMOutletIndex
RPMOutletIndex.description: The unique identifier for an RPM outlet.

slcNetEthIfNumber.name: slcNetEthIfNumber
slcNetEthIfNumber.description: The number of entries in the Ethernet interface table.

slcNetEthIfTable.name: slcNetEthIfTable
slcNetEthIfTable.description: Table of Ethernet network entries. The number of entries is given by the value of slcNetEthIfNumber.

slcNetEthIfEntry.name: slcNetEthIfEntry
slcNetEthIfEntry.description: An entry with the attributes for each Ethernet interface. Ethernet Port Eth1 is always index 1, and Eth2 is always index 2.

slcNetEthIfIndex.name: slcNetEthIfIndex
slcNetEthIfIndex.description: Reference index for each Ethernet interface.

slcNetEthIfSource.name: slcNetEthIfSource
slcNetEthIfSource.description: The state/source for the IP Address and subnet mask for the Ethernet interface.

slcNetEthIfMode.name: slcNetEthIfMode
slcNetEthIfMode.description: The speed and duplex for the Ethernet interface.

slcNetEthIfIPv6Addr.name: slcNetEthIfIPv6Addr
slcNetEthIfIPv6Addr.description: The IPv6 Address for each Ethernet interface.

slcNetEthIfIPv6PrefixLength.name: slcNetEthIfIPv6PrefixLength
slcNetEthIfIPv6PrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix for slcNetEthIfIPv6Addr (in bits).

slcNetEthIfMTU.name: slcNetEthIfMTU
slcNetEthIfMTU.description: The Maximum Transmission Unit for the Ethernet interface.

slcNetEthIfMacAddress.name: slcNetEthIfMacAddress
slcNetEthIfMacAddress.description: The MAC Address for the Ethernet interface.

slcNetEthGateway.name: slcNetEthGateway
slcNetEthGateway.description: The gateway for routing non-Eth1 and non-Eth2 network IPv4 traffic.

slcNetEthGatewayPrecedence.name: slcNetEthGatewayPrecedence
slcNetEthGatewayPrecedence.description: The gateway to give precedence to, if both a static gateway is set, and a gateway is acquired via DHCP or a GPRS Modem.

slcNetEthKeepaliveStartProbes.name: slcNetEthKeepaliveStartProbes
slcNetEthKeepaliveStartProbes.description: TCP keepalive timer: number of seconds to wait before sending out the initial probe.

slcNetEthKeepaliveNumberOfProbes.name: slcNetEthKeepaliveNumberOfProbes
slcNetEthKeepaliveNumberOfProbes.description: TCP keepalive timer: number of probes to send out after the initial probe.

slcNetEthKeepaliveInterval.name: slcNetEthKeepaliveInterval
slcNetEthKeepaliveInterval.description: TCP keepalive timer: number of seconds between probes.

slcNetEthIPForwarding.name: slcNetEthIPForwarding
slcNetEthIPForwarding.description: If enabled, IP forwarding is used.

slcNetEthDNS1.name: slcNetEthDNS1
slcNetEthDNS1.description: The IPv4 Address of DNS server #1.

slcNetEthDNS2.name: slcNetEthDNS2
slcNetEthDNS2.description: The IPv4 Address of DNS server #2.

slcNetEthDNS3.name: slcNetEthDNS3
slcNetEthDNS3.description: The IPv4 Address of DNS server #3.

slcNetEthAlternateGateway.name: slcNetEthAlternateGateway
slcNetEthAlternateGateway.description: The alternate gateway for routing non-Eth1 and non-Eth2 network traffic. The alternate gateway is used if an IP Address usually accessible through the default gateway fails to return one or more pings.

slcNetEthPingIPAddress.name: slcNetEthPingIPAddress
slcNetEthPingIPAddress.description: The IP Address to ping to determine if the alternate gateway should be used.

slcNetEthPingInterface.name: slcNetEthPingInterface
slcNetEthPingInterface.description: The Ethernet interface used to determine if the alternate gateway should be used.

slcNetEthPingDelay.name: slcNetEthPingDelay
slcNetEthPingDelay.description: The delay, in seconds, between pings used to determine if the alternate gateway should be used.

slcNetEthPingFailed.name: slcNetEthPingFailed
slcNetEthPingFailed.description: The number of pings with no response required for the alternate gateway to be used.

slcNetEthBonding.name: slcNetEthBonding
slcNetEthBonding.description: The Ethernet network redundancy/load balancing setting.

slcNetEthGatewayIPv6.name: slcNetEthGatewayIPv6
slcNetEthGatewayIPv6.description: The default gateway for routing non-Eth1 and non-Eth2 IPv6 network traffic.

slcNetEthDNS1IPv6.name: slcNetEthDNS1IPv6
slcNetEthDNS1IPv6.description: The IPv6 Address of DNS server #1.

slcNetEthDNS2IPv6.name: slcNetEthDNS2IPv6
slcNetEthDNS2IPv6.description: The IPv6 Address of DNS server #2.

slcNetEthDNS3IPv6.name: slcNetEthDNS3IPv6
slcNetEthDNS3IPv6.description: The IPv6 Address of DNS server #3.

slcNetEthPreferIPv4DNS.name: slcNetEthPreferIPv4DNS
slcNetEthPreferIPv4DNS.description: If enabled, IPv4 DNS records will be preferred when DNS hostname lookups are performed. Otherwise IPv6 records will be preferred (when IPv6 is enabled).

slcNetFirewallState.name: slcNetFirewallState
slcNetFirewallState.description: If enabled, network traffic is filtered.

slcNetFirewallReject.name: slcNetFirewallReject
slcNetFirewallReject.description: If enabled, returns a 'connection denied' message on blocked ports. If disabled, ignores attempts to connect to a blocked port. This object is deprecated.

slcNetFirewallPing.name: slcNetFirewallPing
slcNetFirewallPing.description: If enabled, the SLC is invisible to pings. This object is deprecated.

slcNetFirewallSSH.name: slcNetFirewallSSH
slcNetFirewallSSH.description: If enabled, the SSH port is open. If disabled, the SSH port is blocked to network traffic. This object is deprecated.

slcNetFirewallTelnet.name: slcNetFirewallTelnet
slcNetFirewallTelnet.description: If enabled, the Telnet port is open. If disabled, the Telnet port is blocked to network traffic. This object is deprecated.

slcNetFirewallHTTP.name: slcNetFirewallHTTP
slcNetFirewallHTTP.description: If enabled, the HTTP port is open. If disabled, the HTTP port is blocked to network traffic. This object is deprecated.

slcNetFirewallHTTPS.name: slcNetFirewallHTTPS
slcNetFirewallHTTPS.description: If enabled, the HTTPS port is open. If disabled, the HTTPS port is blocked to network traffic. This object is deprecated.

slcNetFirewallSMBCIFS.name: slcNetFirewallSMBCIFS
slcNetFirewallSMBCIFS.description: If enabled, the SMBCIFS port is open. If disabled, the SMBCIFS port is blocked to network traffic. This object is deprecated.

slcNetFirewallRulesetNumber.name: slcNetFirewallRulesetNumber
slcNetFirewallRulesetNumber.description: The number of entries in the IP Filter Ruleset table.

slcNetFirewallRulesetTable.name: slcNetFirewallRulesetTable
slcNetFirewallRulesetTable.description: Table of IP Filter Rulesets. The number of entries is given by the value of slcNetFirewallRulesetNumber.

slcNetFirewallRulesetEntry.name: slcNetFirewallRulesetEntry
slcNetFirewallRulesetEntry.description: An entry with all the attributes, including the rules, for an IP Filter Ruleset.

slcNetFirewallRulesetIndex.name: slcNetFirewallRulesetIndex
slcNetFirewallRulesetIndex.description: Reference index for each IP Filter Ruleset.

slcNetFirewallRulesetName.name: slcNetFirewallRulesetName
slcNetFirewallRulesetName.description: The name assigned to the IP Filter Ruleset.

slcNetFirewallRulesetNumRules.name: slcNetFirewallRulesetNumRules
slcNetFirewallRulesetNumRules.description: The number of rules in the slcNetFirewallRulesetRules string.

slcNetFirewallRulesetRules.name: slcNetFirewallRulesetRules
slcNetFirewallRulesetRules.description: The IP Filter rules that are defined for the Ruleset. The rule format is <IP>/<Mask Bits>;<Protocol>;<Ports>;<Action> and rules are separated by a colon. If the string is truncated because of system limitations, the string will be terminated with two colons.

slcNetFirewallMappingNumber.name: slcNetFirewallMappingNumber
slcNetFirewallMappingNumber.description: The number of entries in the IP Filter Mapping table.

slcNetFirewallMappingTable.name: slcNetFirewallMappingTable
slcNetFirewallMappingTable.description: Table of mappings between IP Filter Rulesets and interfaces. The number of entries is given by the value of slcNetFirewallMappingNumber.

slcNetFirewallMappingEntry.name: slcNetFirewallMappingEntry
slcNetFirewallMappingEntry.description: An entry defining an interface that has an IP Filter Ruleset assigned to it. The interface can be either an Ethernet interface or a PC Card or Device Port modem.

slcNetFirewallMappingIndex.name: slcNetFirewallMappingIndex
slcNetFirewallMappingIndex.description: Reference index for each IP Filter mapping.

slcNetFirewallMappingIfac.name: slcNetFirewallMappingIfac
slcNetFirewallMappingIfac.description: The interface which has an IP Filter Ruleset assigned to it. If the interface is devicePort or usbPort, slcNetFirewallMappingIfacId defines which Device Port or USB Port (with an attached modem) the Ruleset is assigned to.

slcNetFirewallMappingIfacId.name: slcNetFirewallMappingIfacId
slcNetFirewallMappingIfacId.description: The identifier for a Device Port if slcNetFirewallMappingIfac equals devicePort(5), or the identifier for a USB Port if slcNetFirewallMappingIfac equals usbPort. Otherwise equals zero.

slcNetFirewallMappingRuleset.name: slcNetFirewallMappingRuleset
slcNetFirewallMappingRuleset.description: The name of the IP Filter Ruleset assigned to the interface.

slcNetRouteRIPState.name: slcNetRouteRIPState
slcNetRouteRIPState.description: If enabled, the Routing Information Protocol (RIP) is used.

slcNetRouteRIPVersion.name: slcNetRouteRIPVersion
slcNetRouteRIPVersion.description: The version of RIP being used.

slcNetRouteStaticState.name: slcNetRouteStaticState
slcNetRouteStaticState.description: If enabled, static routing is used.

slcNetRouteStaticNumber.name: slcNetRouteStaticNumber
slcNetRouteStaticNumber.description: The number of entries in the Static Routes table.

slcNetRouteStaticTable.name: slcNetRouteStaticTable
slcNetRouteStaticTable.description: Table of static route entries. The number of entries is given by the value of slcNetRouteStaticNumber.

slcNetRouteStaticEntry.name: slcNetRouteStaticEntry
slcNetRouteStaticEntry.description: An entry with the IP Address, subnet mask, and gateway for a static route.

slcNetRouteStaticIndex.name: slcNetRouteStaticIndex
slcNetRouteStaticIndex.description: Reference index for each static route.

slcNetRouteStaticIP.name: slcNetRouteStaticIP
slcNetRouteStaticIP.description: The IP Address for the static route.

slcNetRouteStaticMask.name: slcNetRouteStaticMask
slcNetRouteStaticMask.description: The subnet mask for the static route.

slcNetRouteStaticGateway.name: slcNetRouteStaticGateway
slcNetRouteStaticGateway.description: The gateway for the static route.

slcNetVPNTunnel.name: slcNetVPNTunnel
slcNetVPNTunnel.description: If enabled, the SLC is configured to initiate a VPN tunnel.

slcNetVPNStatus.name: slcNetVPNStatus
slcNetVPNStatus.description: A string giving the current status of the VPN tunnel.

slcNetVPNName.name: slcNetVPNName
slcNetVPNName.description: The name of the VPN tunnel.

slcNetVPNEthPort.name: slcNetVPNEthPort
slcNetVPNEthPort.description: The Ethernet interface used for the VPN tunnel.

slcNetVPNRemoteHost.name: slcNetVPNRemoteHost
slcNetVPNRemoteHost.description: The IP Address of the host on the remote side of the tunnel.

slcNetVPNRemoteId.name: slcNetVPNRemoteId
slcNetVPNRemoteId.description: How the remote host should be identified for authentication.

slcNetVPNRemoteHop.name: slcNetVPNRemoteHop
slcNetVPNRemoteHop.description: If the remote host is behind a gateway, this specifies the IP Address of the gateway's public network interface.

slcNetVPNRemoteSubnet.name: slcNetVPNRemoteSubnet
slcNetVPNRemoteSubnet.description: One or more subnets behind the remote host, expressed in CIDR notation (IP Address/mask bits). Multiple subnets are separated by a comma.

slcNetVPNLocalId.name: slcNetVPNLocalId
slcNetVPNLocalId.description: How the SLC should be identified for authentication.

slcNetVPNLocalHop.name: slcNetVPNLocalHop
slcNetVPNLocalHop.description: If the SLC is behind a gateway, this specifies the IP Address of the gateway's public network interface.

slcNetVPNLocalSubnet.name: slcNetVPNLocalSubnet
slcNetVPNLocalSubnet.description: One or more subnets behind the SLC, expressed in CIDR notation (IP Address/mask bits). Multiple subnets are separated by a comma.

slcNetVPNIKENegotiation.name: slcNetVPNIKENegotiation
slcNetVPNIKENegotiation.description: The type of mode used by the SLC and the remote host for the IKE protocol, which exchanges security options between two hosts which want to communicate via IPSec.

slcNetVPNIKEEncryption.name: slcNetVPNIKEEncryption
slcNetVPNIKEEncryption.description: The type of encryption used for IKE negotiation.

slcNetVPNIKEAuthentication.name: slcNetVPNIKEAuthentication
slcNetVPNIKEAuthentication.description: The type of authentication used for IKE negotiation.

slcNetVPNIKEDHGroup.name: slcNetVPNIKEDHGroup
slcNetVPNIKEDHGroup.description: The type of Diffie-Hellman Group used for IKE negotiation.

slcNetVPNESPEncryption.name: slcNetVPNESPEncryption
slcNetVPNESPEncryption.description: The type of encryption used for encrypting data sent through the tunnel.

slcNetVPNESPAuthentication.name: slcNetVPNESPAuthentication
slcNetVPNESPAuthentication.description: The type of authentication used for authenticating data sent through the VPN tunnel.

slcNetVPNESPDHGroup.name: slcNetVPNESPDHGroup
slcNetVPNESPDHGroup.description: The type of Diffie-Hellman Group used for the key exchange for data sent through the tunnel.

slcNetVPNAuthentication.name: slcNetVPNAuthentication
slcNetVPNAuthentication.description: The type of authentication used by the host on each side of the tunnel to verify the identify of the other host.

slcNetVPNPerfectForwardSecrecy.name: slcNetVPNPerfectForwardSecrecy
slcNetVPNPerfectForwardSecrecy.description: When a new IPSec SA is negotiated after the IPSec SA lifetime expires, a new Diffie-Hellman key exchange can be performed to generate a new session key to be used to encrypt the data being sent through the tunnel. If this is enabled, it provides greater security, since the old session keys are destroyed.

slcNetVPNModeConfigClient.name: slcNetVPNModeConfigClient
slcNetVPNModeConfigClient.description: If this is enabled, the SLC can receive network configuration from the remote host. This allows the remote host to assign an IP address/netmask to the SLC side of the VPN tunnel.

slcNetVPNXAUTHClient.name: slcNetVPNXAUTHClient
slcNetVPNXAUTHClient.description: If this is enabled, the SLC will send authentication credentials to the remote host if they are requested. XAUTH, or Extended Authentication, can be used as an additional security measure on top of the Pre-Shared Key or RSA Public Key.

slcNetVPNXAUTHClientLogin.name: slcNetVPNXAUTHClientLogin
slcNetVPNXAUTHClientLogin.description: If slcNetVPNXAUTHClientLogin is enabled, this is the login used for authentication.

slcNetSecurityFIPSMode.name: slcNetSecurityFIPSMode
slcNetSecurityFIPSMode.description: If enabled, the SLC is running in FIPS mode.

slcServNTPState.name: slcServNTPState
slcServNTPState.description: If enabled, NTP is used to synchronize SLC time with a network time server.

slcServNTPSynchronize.name: slcServNTPSynchronize
slcServNTPSynchronize.description: The method used by the SLC to synchronize time: receive broadcasts from the NTP server, or poll the NTP server.

slcServNTPPoll.name: slcServNTPPoll
slcServNTPPoll.description: If slcServNTPSynchronize is set to poll, indicates whether a local server or a public server is used as the NTP server.

slcServNTPServer.name: slcServNTPServer
slcServNTPServer.description: The IPv4 Address of the local or public NTP server.

slcServNTPLocalServer2.name: slcServNTPLocalServer2
slcServNTPLocalServer2.description: The IPv4 Address of the 2nd local NTP server.

slcServNTPLocalServer3.name: slcServNTPLocalServer3
slcServNTPLocalServer3.description: The IPv4 Address of the 3rd local NTP server.

slcServNTPServerIPv6.name: slcServNTPServerIPv6
slcServNTPServerIPv6.description: The IPv6 Address of the local NTP server.

slcServNTPLocalServer2IPv6.name: slcServNTPLocalServer2IPv6
slcServNTPLocalServer2IPv6.description: The IPv6 Address of the 2nd local NTP server.

slcServNTPLocalServer3IPv6.name: slcServNTPLocalServer3IPv6
slcServNTPLocalServer3IPv6.description: The IPv6 Address of the 3rd local NTP server.

slcDevPortCfgEmailByteThresh.description: When Token and Data Detection (previously called 'Email Logging') is configured to trigger on a data byte count, the number of bytes required to trigger an action.

slcDevPortCfgEmailDelay.name: slcDevPortCfgEmailDelay
slcDevPortCfgEmailDelay.description: For Token and Data Detection (previously called 'Email Logging'), a time limit of how long the device port will capture data after the data trigger is detected and before closing the log file and performing the selected actions. This setting is now called 'Action Delay'.

slcDevPortCfgEmailRestartDelay.name: slcDevPortCfgEmailRestartDelay
slcDevPortCfgEmailRestartDelay.description: For Token and Data Detection (previously called 'Email Logging'), the period of time, after performing the selected actions, during which the device port will ignore additional characters received.

slcDevPortCfgEmailTextString.name: slcDevPortCfgEmailTextString
slcDevPortCfgEmailTextString.description: When Token and Data Detection (previously called 'Email Logging') is configured to trigger on a character string, this defines the character string that will trigger an action.

slcDevPortCfgEmailTo.name: slcDevPortCfgEmailTo
slcDevPortCfgEmailTo.description: For Token and Data Detection (previously called 'Email Logging'), if the Email action is enabled, this object defines the list of emails to send email notification to.

slcDevPortCfgEmailSubject.name: slcDevPortCfgEmailSubject
slcDevPortCfgEmailSubject.description: For Token and Data Detection (previously called 'Email Logging'), if the Email action is enabled, this object defines the subject to include with email notification.

slcDevPortCfgPCCardState.name: slcDevPortCfgPCCardState
slcDevPortCfgPCCardState.description: If enabled, PC Card logging is enabled for the Device Port. This value will be undefined if the SLC does not have PC Card slots.

slcDevPortCfgPCCardLogTo.name: slcDevPortCfgPCCardLogTo
slcDevPortCfgPCCardLogTo.description: For PC Card logging, which PC Card slot to use for logging. This value will be undefined if the SLC does not have PC Card slots.

slcDevPortCfgPCCardMaxFiles.name: slcDevPortCfgPCCardMaxFiles
slcDevPortCfgPCCardMaxFiles.description: The maximum number of files to use for PC Card logging. This value will be undefined if the SLC does not have PC Card slots.

slcDevPortCfgPCCardMaxSize.name: slcDevPortCfgPCCardMaxSize
slcDevPortCfgPCCardMaxSize.description: The maximum size of each file (in bytes) for PC Card logging. This value will be undefined if the SLC does not have PC Card slots.

slcDevPortCfgAction.name: slcDevPortCfgAction
slcDevPortCfgAction.description: Performs an action on a Device Port. A read of this object always returns the value noAction(1). Setting this object to zeroPortCounters(2) will reset all port counters given in slcDevPortStateTable. Setting this object to clearLocalLog(3) will clear the local logging buffer. Setting this object to terminateConnections(4) will terminate all connections associated with the Device Port.

slcDevPortCfgEmailSend.name: slcDevPortCfgEmailSend
slcDevPortCfgEmailSend.description: When a trigger is received, the type of notification to send: email, SNMP trap, or email and SNMP trap. This object is deprecated; instead refer to slcDevPortCfgTokenAction.

slcDevPortCfgBanner.name: slcDevPortCfgBanner
slcDevPortCfgBanner.description: The banner displayed when the Device Port is connected to via SSH or Telnet.

slcDevPortCfgIdleTimeout.name: slcDevPortCfgIdleTimeout
slcDevPortCfgIdleTimeout.description: The timeout (in seconds) for dial-in and dial-on-demand PPP connections. If no traffic is received for the PPP connection in the time defined by the idle timeout, the PPP connection will be terminated. A value of 0 indicates that timeouts are disabled.

slcDevPortCfgRestartDelay.name: slcDevPortCfgRestartDelay
slcDevPortCfgRestartDelay.description: The delay (in seconds) to wait before restarting dial-out or dial-on-demand PPP connections.

slcDevPortCfgCallerIdLogging.name: slcDevPortCfgCallerIdLogging
slcDevPortCfgCallerIdLogging.description: If enabled, caller id logging is enabled for a modem dial-in connection.

slcDevPortCfgCallerIdATCmd.name: slcDevPortCfgCallerIdATCmd
slcDevPortCfgCallerIdATCmd.description: The modem AT command required to initiate caller id logging by the modem.

slcDevPortCfgDODAuth.name: slcDevPortCfgDODAuth
slcDevPortCfgDODAuth.description: For PPP connections that are configured for both Dial-in and Dial-on-Demand, the type of authentication to be used for Dial-on-Demand.

slcDevPortCfgDODCHAPHost.name: slcDevPortCfgDODCHAPHost
slcDevPortCfgDODCHAPHost.description: For PPP connections that are configured for both Dial-in and Dial-on-Demand, with CHAP authentication for Dial-on-Demand, the host (for Unix) or user (for Windows) to use.

slcDevPortCfgSLMLoggingState.name: slcDevPortCfgSLMLoggingState
slcDevPortCfgSLMLoggingState.description: If enabled, SLM logging is enabled for the Device Port.

slcDevPortCfgSLMNMS.name: slcDevPortCfgSLMNMS
slcDevPortCfgSLMNMS.description: The IP Addresses of up to three SNMP Network Management Stations defined used for SLM Logging. Multiple IP Addresses will be separated by a comma.

slcDevPortCfgSLMByteThresh.name: slcDevPortCfgSLMByteThresh
slcDevPortCfgSLMByteThresh.description: The number of bytes required to trigger SLM logging.

slcDevPortCfgSLMTimeFrame.name: slcDevPortCfgSLMTimeFrame
slcDevPortCfgSLMTimeFrame.description: The time frame for SLM logging, in seconds.

slcDevPortCfgWebColumns.name: slcDevPortCfgWebColumns
slcDevPortCfgWebColumns.description: The number of columns in the Web SSH or Telnet window for this Device Port.

slcDevPortCfgWebRows.name: slcDevPortCfgWebRows
slcDevPortCfgWebRows.description: The number of rows in the Web SSH or Telnet window for this Device Port.

slcDevPortCfgSyslogState.name: slcDevPortCfgSyslogState
slcDevPortCfgSyslogState.description: If enabled, Syslog logging is enabled for the Device Port.

slcDevPortCfgHostList.name: slcDevPortCfgHostList
slcDevPortCfgHostList.description: When slcDevPortCfgModemState is set to dialinHostList, the name of the Host List used for Dial-in.

slcDevPortCfgDevLowTemp.name: slcDevPortCfgDevLowTemp
slcDevPortCfgDevLowTemp.description: The low temperature limit, in Celsius, for the device connected to this Device Port. If the temperature is not applicable, 9999 will be returned.

slcDevPortCfgDevHighTemp.name: slcDevPortCfgDevHighTemp
slcDevPortCfgDevHighTemp.description: The high temperature limit, in Celsius, for the device connected to this Device Port. If the temperature is not applicable, 9999 will be returned.

slcDevPortCfgDevTemperature.name: slcDevPortCfgDevTemperature
slcDevPortCfgDevTemperature.description: The actual temperature, in Celsius, for the device connected to this Device Port. If the temperature is not applicable, an empty string will be returned.

slcDevPortCfgDevLowHumidity.name: slcDevPortCfgDevLowHumidity
slcDevPortCfgDevLowHumidity.description: The low humidty limit, in percentage, for the device connected to this Device Port. If the temperature is not applicable, 9999 will be returned.

slcDevPortCfgDevHighHumidity.name: slcDevPortCfgDevHighHumidity
slcDevPortCfgDevHighHumidity.description: The high humidty limit, in percentage, for the device connected to this Device Port. If the temperature is not applicable, 9999 will be returned.

slcDevPortCfgDevHumidity.name: slcDevPortCfgDevHumidity
slcDevPortCfgDevHumidity.description: The actual humidity, in percentage, for the device connected to this Device Port. If the temperature is not applicable, an empty string will be returned.

slcDevPortCfgDevTraps.name: slcDevPortCfgDevTraps
slcDevPortCfgDevTraps.description: If enabled, traps will be sent when one of the limits for the device connected to this Device Port are exceeded.

slcDevPortCfgShowLines.name: slcDevPortCfgShowLines
slcDevPortCfgShowLines.description: If enabled, upon connecting to the Device Port, a series of characters (or lines) output to the Device Port before it was connected to are displayed.

slcDevPortCfgNumberShowLines.name: slcDevPortCfgNumberShowLines
slcDevPortCfgNumberShowLines.description: If slcDevPortCfgShowLines is enabled, the number of lines that are displayed upon connecting to the Device Port.

slcDevPortCfgViewPortLog.name: slcDevPortCfgViewPortLog
slcDevPortCfgViewPortLog.description: If enabled, upon using 'connect direct' to a Device Port, the slcDevPortCfgPortLogSeq key sequence can be typed to view the end of the port log for the current Device Port, or a different Device Port.

slcDevPortCfgPortLogSeq.name: slcDevPortCfgPortLogSeq
slcDevPortCfgPortLogSeq.description: The character sequence to view the port log for the Device Port.

slcDevPortCfgMaxDirectConnects.name: slcDevPortCfgMaxDirectConnects
slcDevPortCfgMaxDirectConnects.description: The maximum number of direct connects at the CLI for the Device Port.

slcDevPortCfgTelnetTimeout.name: slcDevPortCfgTelnetTimeout
slcDevPortCfgTelnetTimeout.description: The timeout (in seconds) for Telnet connections. A value of 0 indicates that timeouts are disabled.

slcDevPortCfgSSHTimeout.name: slcDevPortCfgSSHTimeout
slcDevPortCfgSSHTimeout.description: The timeout (in seconds) for SSH connections. A value of 0 indicates that timeouts are disabled.

slcDevPortCfgTCPTimeout.name: slcDevPortCfgTCPTimeout
slcDevPortCfgTCPTimeout.description: The timeout (in seconds) for TCP connections. A value of 0 indicates that timeouts are disabled.

slcDevPortCfgCBCPClientType.name: slcDevPortCfgCBCPClientType
slcDevPortCfgCBCPClientType.description: When slcDevPortCfgModemState is set to cbcpClient, the preferred type of dialback number to use for CBCP negotiation.

slcDevPortCfgCBCPServerAllowNoCallback.name: slcDevPortCfgCBCPServerAllowNoCallback
slcDevPortCfgCBCPServerAllowNoCallback.description: If enabled and slcDevPortCfgModemState is set to cbcpServer, the SLC will allow the PPP peer to select the No Callback option during CBCP negotiation.

slcDevPortCfgDialbackDelay.name: slcDevPortCfgDialbackDelay
slcDevPortCfgDialbackDelay.description: When slcDevPortCfgModemState is set to dialback or cbcpServer, specifies the delay between the dial-in and dial-out portion of the dialing sequence.

slcDevPortCfgUSBState.name: slcDevPortCfgUSBState
slcDevPortCfgUSBState.description: If enabled, USB logging is enabled for the Device Port. This value will be undefined if the SLC does not have USB Ports.

slcDevPortCfgUSBLogTo.name: slcDevPortCfgUSBLogTo
slcDevPortCfgUSBLogTo.description: For USB logging, which USB port to use for logging. This value will be undefined if the SLC does not have USB Ports.

slcDevPortCfgUSBMaxFiles.name: slcDevPortCfgUSBMaxFiles
slcDevPortCfgUSBMaxFiles.description: The maximum number of files to use for USB logging. This value will be undefined if the SLC does not have USB Ports.

slcDevPortCfgUSBMaxSize.name: slcDevPortCfgUSBMaxSize
slcDevPortCfgUSBMaxSize.description: The maximum size of each file (in bytes) for USB logging. This value will be undefined if the SLC does not have USB Ports.

slcDevPortCfgCHAPAuthLocalUsers.name: slcDevPortCfgCHAPAuthLocalUsers
slcDevPortCfgCHAPAuthLocalUsers.description: If enabled, the local user list (login and password) is used to validate the CHAP host and secret sent by a remote PPP peer for CHAP authentication, instead of using the CHAP host and secret associated with a modem.

slcDevPortCfgUseSites.name: slcDevPortCfgUseSites
slcDevPortCfgUseSites.description: If enabled, sites (a set of site-oriented modem parameters that can be activated by various modem-related events such as authentication, outbound traffic for Dial-on-demand connections, etc.) will be used instead of the parameters configured for the modem.

slcDevPortCfgDialbackRetries.name: slcDevPortCfgDialbackRetries
slcDevPortCfgDialbackRetries.description: When slcDevPortCfgModemState is set to dialback or cbcpServer, specifies the number of times the SLC will retry the dial-out portion of the dialing sequence if the first attempt to dial-out fails.

slcDevPortCfgGroup.name: slcDevPortCfgGroup
slcDevPortCfgGroup.description: The group or groups that may access the Device Port.

slcDevPortCfgIPMask.name: slcDevPortCfgIPMask
slcDevPortCfgIPMask.description: The network mask associated with slcDevPortCfgIPMask.

slcDevPortCfgDevPrompt.name: slcDevPortCfgDevPrompt
slcDevPortCfgDevPrompt.description: If the device port is connected to a SLP or ServerTech CDU, specifies the prompt that is configured for the SLP or ServerTech CDU. This object is deprecated, and has been replaced by the RPM functionality.

slcDevPortCfgDevNumOutlets.name: slcDevPortCfgDevNumOutlets
slcDevPortCfgDevNumOutlets.description: If the device port is connected to a ServerTech CDU, specifies the number of outlets on the primary/master ServerTech unit. This object is deprecated, and has been replaced by the RPM functionality.

slcDevPortCfgDevNumExpOutlets.name: slcDevPortCfgDevNumExpOutlets
slcDevPortCfgDevNumExpOutlets.description: If the device port is connected to a ServerTech CDU, specifies the number of outlets on the expansion ServerTech unit. This object is deprecated, and has been replaced by the RPM functionality.

slcDevPortCfgReversePinout.name: slcDevPortCfgReversePinout
slcDevPortCfgReversePinout.description: If enabled, swaps the positions of the serial lines, such that the direction of data or the signal is reversed. For instance, TX is swapped with RX. Enabling Reverse Pinout facilitates connections to Cisco and Sun style RS-45 console ports using a straight through Ethernet patch cable, without the need for a rolled cable or adapter. Note that all Lantronix serial adapters are intended to be used with Reverse Pinout disabled.

slcDevPortCfgUSBVBUS.name: slcDevPortCfgUSBVBUS
slcDevPortCfgUSBVBUS.description: For SLC8000 USB Device Ports only. If enabled, the USB VBUS signal provides power to the USB device attached to a device port. Disabling VBUS will power down the device as long as it is bus-powered instead of self-powered.

slcDevPortCfgAssertDTR.name: slcDevPortCfgAssertDTR
slcDevPortCfgAssertDTR.description: For RJ45 Device Ports only. By default, DTR is asserted on a device port nearly all of the time (except momentarily when a port is opened for operations). Unchecking this option will deassert DTR, simulating a cable disconnection for the device that is connected to a device port.

slcDevPortCfgPortType.name: slcDevPortCfgPortType
slcDevPortCfgPortType.description: Indicates the connector type on the device port: RJ45 or USB.

slcDevPortCfgTelnetTimeoutDataDirection.name: slcDevPortCfgTelnetTimeoutDataDirection
slcDevPortCfgTelnetTimeoutDataDirection.description: If slcDevPortCfgTelnetTimeout is enabled, this setting indicates the direction of data used to determine if the connection has timed out.

slcDevPortCfgSSHTimeoutDataDirection.name: slcDevPortCfgSSHTimeoutDataDirection
slcDevPortCfgSSHTimeoutDataDirection.description: If slcDevPortCfgSSHTimeout is enabled, this setting indicates the direction of data used to determine if the connection has timed out.

slcDevPortCfgTCPTimeoutDataDirection.name: slcDevPortCfgTCPTimeoutDataDirection
slcDevPortCfgTCPTimeoutDataDirection.description: If slcDevPortCfgTCPTimeout is enabled, this setting indicates the direction of data used to determine if the connection has timed out.

slcDevPortCfgIdleTimeoutMessage.name: slcDevPortCfgIdleTimeoutMessage
slcDevPortCfgIdleTimeoutMessage.description: If enabled, a message will be displayed to a user when their connection to a device port will be terminated soon due to the connection being idle.

slcDevPortCfgNumberOfSessionsMessage.name: slcDevPortCfgNumberOfSessionsMessage
slcDevPortCfgNumberOfSessionsMessage.description: If enabled, a message will be displayed to a user when connecting to a device port that indicates how many users are currently connected to the device port.

slcDevPortCfgMinimizeLatency.name: slcDevPortCfgMinimizeLatency
slcDevPortCfgMinimizeLatency.description: If enabled, device port latency will be minimized by reducing read delays.

slcDevPortCfgTelnetSoftIAC.name: slcDevPortCfgTelnetSoftIAC
slcDevPortCfgTelnetSoftIAC.description: If enabled, the Telnet server will not block waiting for the initial Telnet protocol IAC option responses.

slcDevPortCfgSendTermString.name: slcDevPortCfgSendTermString
slcDevPortCfgSendTermString.description: If enabled, and a slcDevPortCfgTerminationString is defined, when a network connection to a device port is terminated, the termination string is sent to the device connected to the device port. The string should be defined so that it sends the the appropriate command(s) to the device to terminate any active user sessions.

slcDevPortCfgTerminationString.name: slcDevPortCfgTerminationString
slcDevPortCfgTerminationString.description: The termination string sent to the device connected to the device port if slcDevPortCfgSendTermString is enabled.

slcDevPortCfgPowerManagementSeq.name: slcDevPortCfgPowerManagementSeq
slcDevPortCfgPowerManagementSeq.description: The key sequence that displays the Power Management menu when a user is connected to a device port.

slcDevPortCfgPowerSupplies.name: slcDevPortCfgPowerSupplies
slcDevPortCfgPowerSupplies.description: A string that describes the managed power supplies configured for the device port. A device port can have up to four power supplies that provide power for the device connected to the device port. The string is a comma separated list of power supplies formatted: '<Power Suppy Name>(RPM Id/Outlet Id)'.

slcDevPortCfgToggleDTR.name: slcDevPortCfgToggleDTR
slcDevPortCfgToggleDTR.description: Applies to RJ45 device ports only. If enabled, when a user disconnects from a device port, DTR will be toggled. This feature can be used when a serial connection requires DSR to be active for the attached device to connect. In this case, toggling DTR will end any active connection on the device.

slcDevPortCfgTokenAction.name: slcDevPortCfgTokenAction
slcDevPortCfgTokenAction.description: For Token and Data Detection, a string containing one or more actions that will be performed if a data trigger occurs: syslog, email, trap, sendstring, powersupply.

slcDevPortCfgTokenSendString.name: slcDevPortCfgTokenSendString
slcDevPortCfgTokenSendString.description: For Token and Data Detection (previously called 'Email Logging'), if the Send String action is enabled, this object defines the string to send to the device connected to the device port.

slcDevPortCfgTokenPowerSupply.name: slcDevPortCfgTokenPowerSupply
slcDevPortCfgTokenPowerSupply.description: For Token and Data Detection (previously called 'Email Logging'), if the Control Power Supply action is enabled, this object defines the name of the managed power supply to perform an action on. This string can be 'all' for all managed power supplies associated with the device port, or an individual power supply name.

slcDevPortCfgTokenPowerAction.name: slcDevPortCfgTokenPowerAction
slcDevPortCfgTokenPowerAction.description: For Token and Data Detection (previously called 'Email Logging'), if the Control Power Supply action is enabled, this object defines the action to take on slcDevPortCfgTokenPowerSupply.

slcDevPortStateNumber.name: slcDevPortStateNumber
slcDevPortStateNumber.description: The number of entries in the Device Port State table.

slcDevPortStateTable.name: slcDevPortStateTable
slcDevPortStateTable.description: Table of Device Port state entries. The number of entries is given by the value of slcDevPortStateNumber.

slcDevPortStateEntry.name: slcDevPortStateEntry
slcDevPortStateEntry.description: An entry containing all state information for a Device Port.

slcDevPortStateIndex.name: slcDevPortStateIndex
slcDevPortStateIndex.description: Reference index for each Device Port State entry.

slcDevPortStateBytesInput.name: slcDevPortStateBytesInput
slcDevPortStateBytesInput.description: The number of bytes input to the Device Port since boot or the last time Device Port statistics were zeroed.

slcDevPortStateBytesOutput.name: slcDevPortStateBytesOutput
slcDevPortStateBytesOutput.description: The number of bytes output from the Device Port since boot or the last time Device Port statistics were zeroed.

slcDevPortStateFramingErrors.name: slcDevPortStateFramingErrors
slcDevPortStateFramingErrors.description: The number of framing errors for the Device Port since boot or the last time Device Port statistics were zeroed.

slcDevPortStateParityErrors.name: slcDevPortStateParityErrors
slcDevPortStateParityErrors.description: The number of parity errors for the Device Port since boot or the last time Device Port statistics were zeroed.

slcDevPortStateOverrunErrors.name: slcDevPortStateOverrunErrors
slcDevPortStateOverrunErrors.description: The number of overrun errors for the Device Port since boot or the last time Device Port statistics were zeroed.

slcDevPortStateFlowControlViolations.name: slcDevPortStateFlowControlViolations
slcDevPortStateFlowControlViolations.description: The number of flow control violations for the Device Port since boot or the last time Device Port statistics were zeroed.

slcDevPortStateDSR.name: slcDevPortStateDSR
slcDevPortStateDSR.description: If enabled, Data Set Ready is enabled for the Device Port.

slcDevPortStateDTR.name: slcDevPortStateDTR
slcDevPortStateDTR.description: If enabled, Data Terminal Ready is enabled for the Device Port.

slcDevPortStateCTS.name: slcDevPortStateCTS
slcDevPortStateCTS.description: If enabled, Clear To Send is enabled for the Device Port.

slcDevPortStateRTS.name: slcDevPortStateRTS
slcDevPortStateRTS.description: If enabled, Request To Send is enabled for the Device Port.

slcDevPortStateCD.name: slcDevPortStateCD
slcDevPortStateCD.description: If enabled, Carrier Detect is enabled for the Device Port.

slcPCCardCfgTable.name: slcPCCardCfgTable
slcPCCardCfgTable.description: Table of PC Card configuration entries. There are two entries in the table, index (1) for the upper PC Card slot, and index (2) for the lower PC Card slot. This table will be empty if the SLC does not have PC Card slots.

slcPCCardCfgEntry.name: slcPCCardCfgEntry
slcPCCardCfgEntry.description: An entry containing all configuration settings for a PC Card Slot.

slcPCCardCfgIndex.name: slcPCCardCfgIndex
slcPCCardCfgIndex.description: Reference index for each PC Card Configuration entry.

slcPCCardCfgCardType.name: slcPCCardCfgCardType
slcPCCardCfgCardType.description: The type of PC Card in the slot.

slcPCCardCfgCardId.name: slcPCCardCfgCardId
slcPCCardCfgCardId.description: The identifying string of the card in the slot.

slcPCCardCfgBaud.name: slcPCCardCfgBaud
slcPCCardCfgBaud.description: For ISDN and modem cards, the baud rate.

slcPCCardCfgDataBits.name: slcPCCardCfgDataBits
slcPCCardCfgDataBits.description: For ISDN and modem cards, the data bits.

slcPCCardCfgStopBits.name: slcPCCardCfgStopBits
slcPCCardCfgStopBits.description: For ISDN and modem cards, the stop bits.

slcPCCardCfgParity.name: slcPCCardCfgParity
slcPCCardCfgParity.description: For ISDN and modem cards, the parity.

slcPCCardCfgFlowControl.name: slcPCCardCfgFlowControl
slcPCCardCfgFlowControl.description: For ISDN and modem cards, the flow control.

slcPCCardCfgModemState.name: slcPCCardCfgModemState
slcPCCardCfgModemState.description: For ISDN and modem cards, indicates how the modem will be used.

slcPCCardCfgModemMode.name: slcPCCardCfgModemMode
slcPCCardCfgModemMode.description: For ISDN and modem cards, the mode: PPP (for Dial-in and Dial-out) and text (for Dial-in and Dial-back).

slcPCCardCfgLocalIP.name: slcPCCardCfgLocalIP
slcPCCardCfgLocalIP.description: For PPP connections, the local IP Address (all zeros if it should be negotiated).

slcPCCardCfgRemoteIP.name: slcPCCardCfgRemoteIP
slcPCCardCfgRemoteIP.description: For PPP connections, the remote IP Address (all zeros if it should be negotiated).

slcPCCardCfgAuth.name: slcPCCardCfgAuth
slcPCCardCfgAuth.description: For PPP connections, the type of authentication to be used.

slcPCCardCfgCHAPHost.name: slcPCCardCfgCHAPHost
slcPCCardCfgCHAPHost.description: For PPP connections with CHAP authentication, the host (for Unix) or user (for Windows) to use.

slcPCCardCfgInitScript.name: slcPCCardCfgInitScript
slcPCCardCfgInitScript.description: The initialization script for an external modem.

slcPCCardCfgTimeout.name: slcPCCardCfgTimeout
slcPCCardCfgTimeout.description: The timeout (in minutes) for text connections. A value of 0 indicates that timeouts are disabled.

slcPCCardCfgDialoutNum.name: slcPCCardCfgDialoutNum
slcPCCardCfgDialoutNum.description: The phone number to use for dial-out connections.

slcPCCardCfgDialoutLogin.name: slcPCCardCfgDialoutLogin
slcPCCardCfgDialoutLogin.description: The login to use for dial-out connections.

slcPCCardCfgDialbackMode.name: slcPCCardCfgDialbackMode
slcPCCardCfgDialbackMode.description: For dial-back connections, defines the phone number to call: a number associated with the authenticated user, or a fixed number associated with the Device Port.

slcPCCardCfgDialbackNum.name: slcPCCardCfgDialbackNum
slcPCCardCfgDialbackNum.description: The phone number to use for dial-back connections.

slcPCCardCfgNATState.name: slcPCCardCfgNATState
slcPCCardCfgNATState.description: If enabled, use NAT (Network Address Translation) to allow dial-in and dial-back users to access the network connected to Eth1 and Eth2.

slcPCCardCfgStorageFS.name: slcPCCardCfgStorageFS
slcPCCardCfgStorageFS.description: For storage cards, the type of filesystem on the card.

slcPCCardCfgISDNChannel.name: slcPCCardCfgISDNChannel
slcPCCardCfgISDNChannel.description: The channel on the ISDN card to use, either 1 or 2.

slcPCCardCfgISDNChannelNum.name: slcPCCardCfgISDNChannelNum
slcPCCardCfgISDNChannelNum.description: The phone number associated with the selected ISDN channel.

slcPCCardCfgTelnetState.name: slcPCCardCfgTelnetState
slcPCCardCfgTelnetState.description: If enabled, Telnet connections to the modem/ISDN PC Card are allowed.

slcPCCardCfgTelnetPort.name: slcPCCardCfgTelnetPort
slcPCCardCfgTelnetPort.description: TCP Port number for Telnet connections directly to the modem/ISDN PC Card.

slcPCCardCfgTelnetAuth.name: slcPCCardCfgTelnetAuth
slcPCCardCfgTelnetAuth.description: If enabled, the user is required to authenticate to access the modem/ISDN PC Card with Telnet.

slcPCCardCfgSSHState.name: slcPCCardCfgSSHState
slcPCCardCfgSSHState.description: If enabled, SSH connections to the modem/ISDN PC Card are allowed.

slcPCCardCfgSSHPort.name: slcPCCardCfgSSHPort
slcPCCardCfgSSHPort.description: TCP Port number for SSH connections directly to the modem/ISDN PC Card.

slcPCCardCfgSSHAuth.name: slcPCCardCfgSSHAuth
slcPCCardCfgSSHAuth.description: If enabled, the user is required to authenticate to access the modem/ISDN PC Card with SSH.

slcPCCardCfgTCPState.name: slcPCCardCfgTCPState
slcPCCardCfgTCPState.description: If enabled, TCP connections to the modem/ISDN PC Card are allowed.

slcPCCardCfgTCPPort.name: slcPCCardCfgTCPPort
slcPCCardCfgTCPPort.description: TCP Port number for TCP connections directly to the modem/ISDN PC Card.

slcPCCardCfgTCPAuth.name: slcPCCardCfgTCPAuth
slcPCCardCfgTCPAuth.description: If enabled, the user is required to authenticate to access the modem/ISDN PC Card with TCP.

slcPCCardCfgGSMPIN.name: slcPCCardCfgGSMPIN
slcPCCardCfgGSMPIN.description: The PIN associated with the GSM/GPRS PC Card modem.

slcPCCardCfgGSMNetworkName.name: slcPCCardCfgGSMNetworkName
slcPCCardCfgGSMNetworkName.description: The Network Name associated with the GSM/GPRS PC Card modem.

slcPCCardCfgGSMPPPCompression.name: slcPCCardCfgGSMPPPCompression
slcPCCardCfgGSMPPPCompression.description: If enabled, PPP compression is enabled for GSM/GPRS PC Card modem connections.

slcPCCardCfgGSMAutoAcquireDNS.name: slcPCCardCfgGSMAutoAcquireDNS
slcPCCardCfgGSMAutoAcquireDNS.description: If enabled, DNS servers will be acquired vi GSM/GPRS PC Card modem PPP connections.

slcDevRPMId.description: The unique identifier for an RPM device.

slcDevRPMVendorModel.name: slcDevRPMVendorModel
slcDevRPMVendorModel.description: The manufacture and model of the RPM.

slcDevRPMManagedVia.name: slcDevRPMManagedVia
slcDevRPMManagedVia.description: The method of control for managing the RPM.

slcDevRPMIPAddress.name: slcDevRPMIPAddress
slcDevRPMIPAddress.description: For SNMP and network managed RPMs, the IP Address of the RPM.

slcDevRPMPort.name: slcDevRPMPort
slcDevRPMPort.description: For network managed RPMs, the TCP port to use to connect to the RPM. For USB managed RPMs, the USB port the device is connected to (0 indicates a port on the front of the SLC). For serially managed RPMs, the RJ45 device port the device is connected to.

slcDevRPMDriverOpts.name: slcDevRPMDriverOpts
slcDevRPMDriverOpts.description: Any driver options that are configured for the RPM. This option is mostly used for the USB vendor and product id.

slcDevRPMStatus.name: slcDevRPMStatus
slcDevRPMStatus.description: The current status for the RPM; for example, 'OL' to indicate 'Online' for a UPS. This object may be blank if the device does not report a status, or if the device is not in an error state.

slcDevRPMFirmwareVersion.name: slcDevRPMFirmwareVersion
slcDevRPMFirmwareVersion.description: The current firmware version of the RPM. This object may be blank if the device does not report its firmware version.

slcDevRPMSerialNumber.name: slcDevRPMSerialNumber
slcDevRPMSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the RPM. This object may be blank if the device does not report its serial number.

slcDevRPMMACAddress.name: slcDevRPMMACAddress
slcDevRPMMACAddress.description: The hardware address of the ethernet port of the RPM. This object may be blank if the device does not report its MAC address.

slcDevRPMNumOutlets.name: slcDevRPMNumOutlets
slcDevRPMNumOutlets.description: The number of power outlets that the RPM has.

slcDevRPMOutletsOn.name: slcDevRPMOutletsOn
slcDevRPMOutletsOn.description: The number of RPM outlets that are currently turned on. A negative value indicates that the RPM does not report how many outlets are turned on.

slcDevRPMSNMPReadComm.name: slcDevRPMSNMPReadComm
slcDevRPMSNMPReadComm.description: For SNMP managed RPMs, the SNMP read (get) community.

slcDevRPMAdminLogin.name: slcDevRPMAdminLogin
slcDevRPMAdminLogin.description: For serial or network managed RPMs, the administrator login.

slcDevRPMLogStatus.name: slcDevRPMLogStatus
slcDevRPMLogStatus.description: Indicates how frequently the status for the RPM is logged. A value of 0 indicates that logging is disabled.

slcDevRPMCriticalSNMPTraps.name: slcDevRPMCriticalSNMPTraps
slcDevRPMCriticalSNMPTraps.description: If enabled, indicates that the slcEventRPMAction trap will be sent for critical events for the RPM.

slcDevRPMCriticalEmails.name: slcDevRPMCriticalEmails
slcDevRPMCriticalEmails.description: An email address to send emails to for critical events for the RPM.

slcDevRPMProvidesSLCPower.name: slcDevRPMProvidesSLCPower
slcDevRPMProvidesSLCPower.description: If enabled, indicates that the RPM provides power to the SLC.

slcDevRPMOnLowBattery.name: slcDevRPMOnLowBattery
slcDevRPMOnLowBattery.description: Indicates the action taken when a UPS is on battery and reaches a 'low battery' state. Applies to UPS devices only.

slcDevRPMShutdownOrder.name: slcDevRPMShutdownOrder
slcDevRPMShutdownOrder.description: If a UPS reaches a 'low battery' state and its slcDevRPMOnLowBattery setting is shutdownAllUPS, this indicates the order in which this RPM will be shutdown as all UPSes are shutdown. All UPSes with a shutdown order of '1' will be shutdown first, followed by all UPSes with a shutdown order of '2', etc. Shutdown orders are in the range of 1 to 49, with 50 being reserved for UPSes that provide power to the SLC - they will always be shutdown last. A value of 0 indicates that this UPS will not be shutdown. Applies to UPS devices only.

slcDevRPMLoad.name: slcDevRPMLoad
slcDevRPMLoad.description: The current load of the RPM expressed as a percentage. The value is in tenths of a percent. A negative value indicates that the RPM does not report load values.

slcDevRPMLoadOverThreshold.name: slcDevRPMLoadOverThreshold
slcDevRPMLoadOverThreshold.description: The load when the RPM switches to an overload condition, expressed as a percentage. The value is in tenths of a percent. A negative value indicates that the RPM does not report over load threshold values.

slcDevRPMBatteryCharge.name: slcDevRPMBatteryCharge
slcDevRPMBatteryCharge.description: The current battery charge for the the RPM, expressed as a percentage. The value is in tenths of a percent. A negative value indicates that the RPM does not report battery charge values.

slcDevRPMBatteryRuntime.name: slcDevRPMBatteryRuntime
slcDevRPMBatteryRuntime.description: The number of seconds in the RPM remaining battery life. A value of 0 indicates that the RPM does not report battery runtime values.

slcDevRPMBeeperStatus.name: slcDevRPMBeeperStatus
slcDevRPMBeeperStatus.description: If enabled, indicates that the RPM beeper is enabled. A value of 0 indicates that the RPM does not report beeper status.

slcDevRPMTemperature.name: slcDevRPMTemperature

slcDevRPMUptime.name: slcDevRPMUptime

slcDevRPMCurrent.name: slcDevRPMCurrent

slcDevRPMInputVoltage.name: slcDevRPMInputVoltage

slcDevRPMApparentPower.name: slcDevRPMApparentPower

slcDevRPMNominalApparentPower.name: slcDevRPMNominalApparentPower

slcDevRPMRealPower.name: slcDevRPMRealPower
slcDevRPMRealPower.description: The real power, in tenths of Watts, on a given RPM tower or unit. If the value is negative, the RPM does not report real power for the tower or unit.

slcDevRPMNominalRealPower.name: slcDevRPMNominalRealPower
slcDevRPMNominalRealPower.description: The nominal real power, in tenths of Watts, on a given RPM tower or unit. If the value is negative, the RPM does not report nominal real power for the tower or unit.

slcDevRPMOutletTable.name: slcDevRPMOutletTable
slcDevRPMOutletTable.description: Table of RPM outlet status and control entries.

slcDevRPMOutletEntry.name: slcDevRPMOutletEntry
slcDevRPMOutletEntry.description: An entry containing status and control for outlets on an RPM.

slcDevRPMOutletName.name: slcDevRPMOutletName
slcDevRPMOutletName.description: The current name of the RPM outlet. This will be blank if the RPM device does not report outlet names.

slcDevRPMOutletState.name: slcDevRPMOutletState
slcDevRPMOutletState.description: The current state of the RPM outlet.

slcDevRPMOutletCurrent.name: slcDevRPMOutletCurrent
slcDevRPMOutletCurrent.description: The current level, in tenths of Amps, for the RPM outlet. This will be negative if the RPM does not report current values for the outlet.

slcDevRPMOutletAction.name: slcDevRPMOutletAction
slcDevRPMOutletAction.description: Performs an action to change the state of an outlet on an RPM. A read of this object always returns the value noAction(1). If the RPM supports individual outlet control, a command will be sent to the RPM to change the outlet state. Requests for invalid outlets or RPMs that do not support individual outlet control will return an error.

slcConnNumber.name: slcConnNumber
slcConnNumber.description: The number of entries in the Connections table.

slcConnTable.name: slcConnTable
slcConnTable.description: Table of connection entries. The number of entries is given by the value of slcConnNumber.

slcConnEndPt1.name: slcConnEndPt1
slcConnEndPt1.description: A description of one of the end points of the connection.

slcConnEndPt2.name: slcConnEndPt2
slcConnEndPt2.description: A description of one of the end points of the connection.

slcConnFlow.name: slcConnFlow
slcConnFlow.description: The direction that data is flowing in the connection.

slcConnUser.name: slcConnUser
slcConnUser.description: The user that initiated the connection.

slcConnDuration.name: slcConnDuration
slcConnDuration.description: The duration, in seconds, that the connection has existed.

slcConnDurationStr.name: slcConnDurationStr
slcConnDurationStr.description: The duration, formatted in hours:minutes:seconds, that the connection has existed.

slcConnIdle.name: slcConnIdle
slcConnIdle.description: The amount of time that the connection has been idle, in seconds.

slcConnIdleStr.name: slcConnIdleStr
slcConnIdleStr.description: The amount of time that the connection has been idle, formatted in hours:minutes:seconds.

slcConnSourceIP.name: slcConnSourceIP
slcConnSourceIP.description: For network (Telnet and SSH) connections into the SLC, the source IP Address.

slcSystemModel.name: slcSystemModel
slcSystemModel.description: The model of the SLC: SLC8, SLC16, SLC32, SLC48, SLC8008, SLC8016, SLC8024, SLC8032, SLC8040, SLC8048.

slcSystemSerialNo.name: slcSystemSerialNo
slcSystemSerialNo.description: The serial number of the SLC.

slcSystemFWRev.name: slcSystemFWRev
slcSystemFWRev.description: The firmware version of the SLC.

slcSystemLoadVia.name: slcSystemLoadVia
slcSystemLoadVia.description: The method used for firmware updates.

slcSystemFTPServer.name: slcSystemFTPServer
slcSystemFTPServer.description: The IP Address of the FTP/TFTP server used for firmware updates, and for saving and restoring configurations.

slcSystemFTPPath.name: slcSystemFTPPath
slcSystemFTPPath.description: The path on the FTP server used for firmware updates, and for saving and restoring configurations.

slcSystemKeypadLock.name: slcSystemKeypadLock
slcSystemKeypadLock.description: If enabled, the LCD keypad is locked for editing configuration. The keys can only be used to view settings.

slcSystemTimeZone.name: slcSystemTimeZone
slcSystemTimeZone.description: The time zone of the SLC.

slcSystemWelcomeBanner.name: slcSystemWelcomeBanner
slcSystemWelcomeBanner.description: The banner displayed before the login prompt.

slcSystemLoginBanner.name: slcSystemLoginBanner
slcSystemLoginBanner.description: The banner displayed after successful login.

slcSystemWebTimeout.name: slcSystemWebTimeout
slcSystemWebTimeout.description: The timeout (in minutes) for web sessions. A value of 0 indicates that timeouts are disabled.

slcSystemWebGadget.name: slcSystemWebGadget
slcSystemWebGadget.description: If enabled, iGoogle Gadget web content is enabled.

slcSystemAction.name: slcSystemAction
slcSystemAction.description: Performs an action on the SLC. A read of this object always returns the value noAction(1). Setting this object to rebootSLC(2) will terminate all connections and reboot the SLC. Setting this object to shutdownSLC(3) will terminate all connections and shutdown the SLC so it can be powered off.

slcSystemSSHPreAuthBanner.name: slcSystemSSHPreAuthBanner
slcSystemSSHPreAuthBanner.description: The banner displayed prior to SSH authentication.

slcSystemSiteRackRow.name: slcSystemSiteRackRow
slcSystemSiteRackRow.description: The identifier of the row of racks in a data center containing the SLC.

slcSystemSiteRackCluster.name: slcSystemSiteRackCluster
slcSystemSiteRackCluster.description: The identifier of the group of racks in a given row (slcSystemSiteRackRow) containing the SLC.

slcSystemSiteRack.name: slcSystemSiteRack
slcSystemSiteRack.description: The identifier of the rack in a given rack group (slcSystemSiteRackCluster) containing the SLC.

slcSystemLCDScreens.name: slcSystemLCDScreens
slcSystemLCDScreens.description: A string describing the enabled LCD screens, in the order they are displayed. Each screen is separated by a comma. The possible screens are Current Time, Network, Console, Release, Date/Time, Device Ports, Location, Temperature and User Strings.

slcSystemLCDUserStrLine1.name: slcSystemLCDUserStrLine1
slcSystemLCDUserStrLine1.description: For the LCD screen User Strings, this is the first line displayed on the LCD.

slcSystemLCDUserStrLine2.name: slcSystemLCDUserStrLine2
slcSystemLCDUserStrLine2.description: For the LCD screen User Strings, this is the second line displayed on the LCD.

slcSystemLCDScrolling.name: slcSystemLCDScrolling
slcSystemLCDScrolling.description: If enabled, the LCD automatically scrolls through the enabled screens.

slcSystemLCDScrollDelay.name: slcSystemLCDScrollDelay
slcSystemLCDScrollDelay.description: If LCD scrolling is enabled (slcSystemLCDScrolling), the delay in seconds between displaying screens.

slcSystemLCDIdleDelay.name: slcSystemLCDIdleDelay
slcSystemLCDIdleDelay.description: If LCD scrolling is enabled (slcSystemLCDScrolling), the number of seconds after keypad input before auto-scrolling restarts.

slcSystemInternalTemp.name: slcSystemInternalTemp
slcSystemInternalTemp.description: The internal temperature of the SLC, given in Celsius. A value of 9999 is returned if an error is encountered reading the temperature.

slcSystemWebProtocol.name: slcSystemWebProtocol
slcSystemWebProtocol.description: The protocol used by the web server. This setting is no longer available; the web server is configured to only support the TLS protocol.

slcSystemWebCipher.name: slcSystemWebCipher
slcSystemWebCipher.description: The strength of the cipher used by the web server. A cipher with high strength uses 256, 168 or 128 bits; a cipher with medium strength uses 128 bits; a cipher with low strength uses 64 or 56 bits.

slcSystemModelString.name: slcSystemModelString
slcSystemModelString.description: A string that describes the SLC model: <Model>-<Power Supply>-<PCCard or USB>

slcSystemWebGroup.name: slcSystemWebGroup
slcSystemWebGroup.description: The group or groups that may access the web.

slcSystemWebInterface.name: slcSystemWebInterface
slcSystemWebInterface.description: A string describing the interfaces the web is available on; for example: Eth1,Eth2,PPP.

slcSystemWebBanner.name: slcSystemWebBanner
slcSystemWebBanner.description: The banner on the web home page.

slcSystemInternalTempLow.name: slcSystemInternalTempLow
slcSystemInternalTempLow.description: The minimum acceptable internal temperature for the SLC, in Celsius.

slcSystemInternalTempHigh.name: slcSystemInternalTempHigh
slcSystemInternalTempHigh.description: The maximum acceptable internal temperature for the SLC, in Celsius.

slcSystemCalibrateTemp.name: slcSystemCalibrateTemp
slcSystemCalibrateTemp.description: An offset in Celsius for calibrating the internal temperature of the SLC.

slcSystemWebServer.name: slcSystemWebServer
slcSystemWebServer.description: If enabled, the web server will run and listen on TCP ports 80 and 443 (all requests to port 80 are redirected to port 443).

slcPowerSupplyId.name: slcPowerSupplyId
slcPowerSupplyId.description: The identifier of the power supply in a slcEventPowerSupply trap.

slcPowerSupplyAction.name: slcPowerSupplyAction
slcPowerSupplyAction.description: The action that occurred for a power supply in a slcEventPowerSupply trap.

slcDevPortNumBytes.name: slcDevPortNumBytes
slcDevPortNumBytes.description: The number of bytes received on a Device Port to trigger a slcEventDevicePortData or slcEventDevicePortSLMData trap.

slcDevPortData.name: slcDevPortData
slcDevPortData.description: The character data received on a Device Port to trigger a slcEventDevicePortData trap.

slcDevPortStartByte.name: slcDevPortStartByte
slcDevPortStartByte.description: The starting byte within the logging buffer of data received on a Device Port, which triggered a slcEventDevicePortSLMData trap.

slcDevPortTimeFrame.name: slcDevPortTimeFrame
slcDevPortTimeFrame.description: The time frame, in seconds, after which a slcEventDevicePortSLMData trap is sent to the SLM to trigger retrieval of Device Port data.

slcDevPortDeviceErrorStatus.name: slcDevPortDeviceErrorStatus
slcDevPortDeviceErrorStatus.description: The status returned when an error occurs in a device connected to a Device Port.

slcHostname.name: slcHostname
slcHostname.description: The hostname of the SLC sending the trap.

slcPCCardSlot.name: slcPCCardSlot
slcPCCardSlot.description: The PC Card slot indicated for the trap.

slcPCCardAction.name: slcPCCardAction
slcPCCardAction.description: The action that occurred on a PC Card slot.

slcPCCardType.name: slcPCCardType
slcPCCardType.description: The type of card inserted in a PC Card slot.

slcUSBAction.name: slcUSBAction
slcUSBAction.description: The action that occurred on a USB Port.

slcUSBType.name: slcUSBType
slcUSBType.description: The type of device inserted in a USB Port.

slcDevPortErrorStatus.name: slcDevPortErrorStatus
slcDevPortErrorStatus.description: The status returned when an error occurs in a Device Port. dataDrop applies to a specific Device Port and is sent when a Device Port is required to discard data in order to keep data moving for all connections to the Device Port. invalidIOConfiguration and errorIOModules apply to all Device Ports. invalidIOConfiguration is sent when the I/O modules installed in a SLC are in an invalid configuration. errorIOModules is sent when an error is detected in one or more I/O modules.

slcSDCardAction.name: slcSDCardAction
slcSDCardAction.description: The action that occurred on the SD Card slot.

slcRPMAction.name: slcRPMAction
slcRPMAction.description: The action that occurred on a Remote Power Manager.

slcEventHost.name: slcEventHost
slcEventHost.description: The name or IP address of a host in a SLC event.

slcEventPowerSupply.name: slcEventPowerSupply
slcEventPowerSupply.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a power supply fails or is restored.

slcEventSysadminPassword.name: slcEventSysadminPassword
slcEventSysadminPassword.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the sysadmin user password is changed.

slcEventSLCShutdown.name: slcEventSLCShutdown
slcEventSLCShutdown.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the SLC is shutdown.

slcEventDevicePortData.name: slcEventDevicePortData
slcEventDevicePortData.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when data is received on a Device Port, and the Device Port has been configured to generate a trap when a specified number of bytes (slcDevPortNumBytes) or a specified sequence of bytes (slcDevPortCfgEmailTextString) is received. slcDevPortData is the actual data received.

slcEventDevicePortSLMData.name: slcEventDevicePortSLMData
slcEventDevicePortSLMData.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when data is received on a Device Port, and the Device Port has been configured to generate a trap designated for the Secure Lantronix Management Appliance (SLM) when a specified number of bytes is received or a specified time frame is passed. This trap is only sent to the SLM.

slcEventDevicePortSLMConfig.name: slcEventDevicePortSLMConfig
slcEventDevicePortSLMConfig.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the SLM logging configuration is changed for a Device Port, and the Device Port has been configured to generate a trap designated for the Secure Lantronix Management Appliance (SLM). This trap specifies the new SLM logging configuration for the Device Port, and is only sent to the SLM.

slcEventDevicePortDeviceLowTemp.name: slcEventDevicePortDeviceLowTemp
slcEventDevicePortDeviceLowTemp.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the low temperature limit for a sensor connected to a Device Port is exceeded.

slcEventDevicePortDeviceHighTemp.name: slcEventDevicePortDeviceHighTemp
slcEventDevicePortDeviceHighTemp.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the high temperature limit for a sensor connected to a Device Port is exceeded.

slcEventDevicePortDeviceLowHumidity.name: slcEventDevicePortDeviceLowHumidity
slcEventDevicePortDeviceLowHumidity.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the low humidity limit for a sensor connected to a Device Port is exceeded.

slcEventDevicePortDeviceHighHumidity.name: slcEventDevicePortDeviceHighHumidity
slcEventDevicePortDeviceHighHumidity.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the high humidity limit for a sensor connected to a Device Port is exceeded.

slcEventDevicePortDeviceError.name: slcEventDevicePortDeviceError
slcEventDevicePortDeviceError.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an error occurs on a device connected to a Device Port.

slcEventPCCardAction.name: slcEventPCCardAction
slcEventPCCardAction.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an event occurs on one of the PC Card slots.

slcEventSLCInternalTemp.name: slcEventSLCInternalTemp
slcEventSLCInternalTemp.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the internal temperature of the SLC is outside of the acceptable operating range.

slcEventUSBAction.name: slcEventUSBAction
slcEventUSBAction.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an event occurs on one of the USB Ports.

slcEventDevicePortError.name: slcEventDevicePortError
slcEventDevicePortError.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an error occurs on a a Device Port, or across all Device Ports. If an error occurs across all Device Ports, slcDevPortId will be 1 (one).

slcEventSDCardAction.name: slcEventSDCardAction
slcEventSDCardAction.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an event occurs on the SD Card slot.

slcEventNoDialToneAlarm.name: slcEventNoDialToneAlarm
slcEventNoDialToneAlarm.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an event indicates that a no-dial-tone condition on the internal modem exists.

slcEventRPMAction.name: slcEventRPMAction
slcEventRPMAction.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an event occurs on one of the Remote Power Manager (UPS or PDU) devices.

slcEventPingHostFails.name: slcEventPingHostFails
slcEventPingHostFails.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the SLC is monitoring a host with regular pings and the SLC is unable to ping the host. The trap includes either the name or the IP address of the failed host.
